The National Security Advisor, Tom Donilon, will be traveling to Saudi Arabia and the United Arab Emirates from April 11 to 13. During his visit, he will meet with key leaders in each country, including King Abdullah bin Abdulaziz in Riyadh and Crown Prince Mohammed bin Zayed Al Nahyan in Abu Dhabi. The purpose of the visit is to discuss regional issues and emphasize the importance of the relationship between the United States and these two partners.